      • KEY_COMPOBJ

        protected static final java.lang.String KEY_COMPOBJ
        KEY used in the Properties object passed between processors. If this KEY exists in the Properties object then chained processors know the first processor has already completed the component search and it does NOT need to be done again.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • testObjectCache

        protected static java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> testObjectCache
        local cache for containing the test objects. This cache contains pairs as > Note: Don't manipulate it directly like testObjectCache.get(key) etc.
        Use the cache-manipulation-methods defined in AbstractProcessor

      • extractComponentProperties

        protected boolean extractComponentProperties(java.util.Properties props)
        Load our local component name and recognition static fields with the property string values from:

        winname = KEY_WINNAME,
        compname = KEY_COMPNAME,
        winrec = KEY_WINREC,
        comprec = KEY_COMPREC,
        command_timeout = PARAM_TIMEOUT

        Parameters:
        props -
        Returns:
        true if all were retrievable. If any were not present (except command_timeout) then the routine will set appropriate resourceMsg values and setGeneralErrorWithBundleMessage(Properties, ResourceMessageInfo, ResourceMessageInfo) and return false.

      • getSolo

        public com.robotium.solo.Solo getSolo()
        Return the Solo object contained in testrunner
        Attention:
        Only after the method RobotiumTestRunner.launchApplication() has been
        called, the Solo object can be initialized.
        Before, the Solo object is null.
        Returns:
        Solo object or null if the Solo object is not ready.
        See Also:
        RobotiumTestRunner.launchApplication()

      • setGeneralSuccessWithBundleMessage

        protected void setGeneralSuccessWithBundleMessage(java.util.Properties props,
                                      ResourceMessageInfo message,
                                      ResourceMessageInfo detailMessage)
        set the isremoteresult to "true"
        set the remoteresultcode to a constant code Message.STATUS_REMOTERESULT_OK_STRING
        Note: This method will concatenate AbstractProcessor.remoteCommand with
        SoloMessage.RESULT_INFO_GENERAL_SUCCESS
        and set this string to remoteresultinfo
        set the 'resource bundle information', so that the remote-controller can log NLS message.
        Parameters:
        props - The Properties object containing the in and out parameters
        message - ResourceMessageInfo, information about the resource bundle message
        detailMessage - ResourceMessageInfo, information about the resource bundle detail message
        See Also:
        #setResourceBundleInformation(Properties, ResourceMessageInfo, ResourceMessageInfo))
